    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1958-05-06T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1958-05-06T17:00:00-05:00" n="19"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d19">
                <head>19. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d19fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, 783A.00/5–658. Top Secret; Niact. Also sent to Beirut.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Copenhagen</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1958-05-06T23:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 6, 1958—11 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Dulte 10. Re Tedul 8 and Tosec 29.<note n="2" xml:id="d19fn2">Tosec 29 to
                        Copenhagen, May 5, repeated to the Secretary the texts of telegrams 3673 and
                        3674 from Beirut. (<hi rend="italic">Ibid.,</hi> Conference Files: Lot 63 D
                        123, CF 1505) Telegram 3674 is <ref target="#d18">
                            <hi rend="italic">supra</hi>
                        </ref>, and telegram 3673 is summarized in <ref target="#d18fn2">footnote 2,
                                <hi rend="italic">supra</hi>
                        </ref>. Tedul 8 to Copenhagen, May 5, from <persName corresp="#p_HCAJ1"
                            >Herter</persName> to <persName corresp="#p_DAW1">Dulles</persName>,
                        also sent to Beirut as telegram 4173, suggested that, in view of the short
                        time remaining before <persName corresp="#p_MCRM1">McClintock</persName>’s
                        May 7 meeting with <persName corresp="#p_CC7">Chamoun</persName>, <persName
                            corresp="#p_DJF1">Dulles</persName> should coordinate a U.S.–U.K.–French
                        position on the impending Lebanese presidential election with <persName
                            corresp="#p_LJSB1">Selwyn Lloyd</persName> and the French representative
                        at the <gloss target="#t_NATO1">NATO</gloss> meeting in Copenhagen. [<hi
                            rend="italic">3½ lines of text not declassified</hi>] (Department of
                        State, Central Files, 783A.11/5–558; included in <ref
                            target="frus1958-60v11mSupp">the microfiche supplement</ref>)</note>
                    After conferring with Mr. <persName corresp="#p_LJSB1">Lloyd</persName> and Mr.
                        <persName>Laloy</persName> we agree with basic policy decision to support
                        <persName corresp="#p_CC7">Chamoun</persName> on basis of paragraph 3 of
                    joint appreciation<note n="3" xml:id="d19fn3">Transmitted in telegram 3674, <ref
                            target="#d18">
                            <hi rend="italic">supra</hi>
                        </ref>.</note> of British, French and American Ambassadors.</p>
                <pb facs="0063" n="31" xml:id="pg_31"/>
                <p>Secretary leaves to Department and Embassy the implementing of this basic
                    decision in accord with British and French but suggests that if we do back
                        <persName corresp="#p_CC7">Chamoun</persName> we should do so wholeheartedly
                    and possibly Tedul 8 might be somewhat depressing for <persName corresp="#p_CC7"
                        >Chamoun</persName>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DJF1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
